  "description": [
    "PAGE EIGHT Hl ABRAHAM LINCOLN Lincoln and Douglass met the challenge of the slaveholders with the battlecry A Nation cannot exist halfslave and halffree Today it is not only our Nation but the whole world that is engaged in titanic struggle to decide the issue freedom or slavery The American people have risen again in their might as in the days of the Civil War to hurl back the challenge of the 20th centuy Miw cracy And it is in everlasting glory to the Negro people that Negro men and women are fighting valiantly in the armies of freedom even as their forbears fought as heroes in the Army of the Republic But as Douglass told Lincoln a man cannot fight with one arm tied behind his back America in 1861 could not win the war to save the Union without the Emancipation Proclamation And America today cannot win the war against fascism unless the Negro people win full equality in American life unless jimcrow lynch law discrimination in the armed forces and color bars in industry are outlawed forever from our democracy So long as the ugly sore of jimcrow is allowed to fester and spread its corruption throughout"
  ],
